The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Mumbai, April 15 (PTI): Four persons were arrested for allegedly abducting an event manager on Tuesday and asking him to settle a loan.           Virendra Kumar, 34, had taken a loan of Rs 1 lakh from one of the accused but had failed to return it in the last six months. Kumar called up a friend and informed him while he was being kidnapped. The friend went to the police.                   
	 Balasore (PTI): India on Wednesday successfully test-fired an improved version of the nuclear-capable Prithvi-II ballistic missile from the Integrated Test Range at Chandipur as part of a user trial by the army. The surface-to-surface missile has a range of 350km.                  
	 Srinagar: The BSF has arrested a Bengali youth moving suspiciously near the Indo-Pak border in Jammu. Chand Lohar, a resident of Hooghly, was arrested on Tuesday, sources said. He was later handed over to police. The DIG of the BSF, J.B. Sangwan, said the youth, around 17 years old, did not appear to be mentally stable.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): A court has issued summons to ADMK chief Jayalalithaa in a defamation case filed against her by the Tamil Nadu government for allegedly accusing chief minister M. Karunanidhi of siphoning off money from the Sri Lankan Relief Fund.
                                                                                                                           
